{
  "texts": [
    "These methods use heuristics to identify potential bug positions and generate repair candidates.",
    "For instance, GenProg [44] uses an extended form of genetic programming to generate program variants that could fix the bugs and retain the required functionalities.",
    "RSRepair [119] employs the mutation techniques used in GenProg and uses random search to generate a fix patch.",
    "ARJA [166] formulates automated program repair as a multi-objective search problem and uses NSGA-II [21] to look for simpler repairs.",
    "One challenge of search-based APR is the costly validation of patches by testing [33]."
  ]
}